### Available Actions
You may execute one of the following functions:
- Click(box=(x1,y1))
- Drag(start=(x1,y1), end=(x2,y2), speed='normal'|'high'): Drag from start to end. *speed* is optional and defaults to 'normal'.
- Scroll(start=(x1,y1), end=(x2,y2), speed='normal'|'high'): Simulate a finger swipe. *speed* is optional and defaults to 'normal'; use 'high' for a fast fling.
    * To scroll DOWN (reveal bottom content): Swipe finger UP (start_y > end_y).
    * To scroll UP (reveal top content): Swipe finger DOWN (start_y < end_y).
    * To scroll LEFT (reveal right content): Swipe finger LEFT (start_x > end_x).
    * To scroll RIGHT (reveal left content): Swipe finger RIGHT (start_x < end_x).
- Type(content='')
- Launch(app='')
- OpenLink(url='')
- InstallApk(source='')
- Uninstall(app='')
- ForceStop(app=''): Quit the app immediately. Use this action preferably to kill/quit/terminate an app.
- Wait()
- Finished(verdict='pass'|'bug'|'blocker', content='')
- LongPress(box=(x1,y1))
- PressBack()
- PressHome()
- PressRecentApps()
- PressEnter()
- ClipboardGet(): Get current clipboard contents
- ClipboardPaste(): Paste current clipboard contents into the focused text field
- ClipboardPut(content=''): Set the clipboard content to the specified value
{% if resources_available %}
- ResourceList(): List the files available in the resources directory that you can stage on the device with FilePut.
- FilePut(source='', dest=''): Copy a resource file onto the device. *source* is a path relative to the resources directory (see ResourceList); *dest* is a destination folder under /sdcard (e.g. 'Pictures', 'Download', 'DCIM', 'Documents', 'Movies'). You may have to refresh or restart the Files or Gallery app afterwards.
- FileList(path=''): List files under /sdcard/<path> on the device. *path* is optional and defaults to the /sdcard root (e.g. path='Pictures').
- FileDelete(path=''): Delete a file under /sdcard (e.g. path='Pictures/cat.jpg').
{% endif %}
